{
  "text_id": "oracc.etcsri.Q001057",
  "corpus": "oracc",
  "title": "E-anatum 05 (RIME 1.09.03.05 composite)",
  "language": "sumerian",
  "translation_source": "ORACC ETCSRI — CC BY-SA 3.0",
  "source_url": "https://oracc.museum.upenn.edu/etcsri/Q001057",
  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) For Ninĝirsu ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.2",
      "line_range": "2",
      "translation": "(i 2) E-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš , whose name was proclaimed by Enlil , given strength by Ninĝirsu , chosen by Nanše in the heart , nourished on rich milk by Ninhursaĝa , called by a propitious name by Inana , given wisdom by Enki , beloved of Dumuzid-Abzu , supported by Hendursaĝ , beloved friend of Lugal-Uruba , child of Aya-kurgal , ruler of Lagaš , restored Ĝirsu for Ninĝirsu . He built the city-wall of Irikug . He built Niĝin for Nanše ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.34",
      "line_range": "34",
      "translation": "(iii 12) E-ana-tum defeated Elam , the marvelous mountain range and piled up a burial mound for it ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.39",
      "line_range": "39",
      "translation": "(iii 17) He defeated Arawa , whose ruler marched with its standard in the vanguard and piled up a burial mound for it ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.45",
      "line_range": "45",
      "translation": "(iii 23) He defeated Umma , and piled up 20 burial mounds for it ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.49",
      "line_range": "49",
      "translation": "(iv 2) He restored his beloved field of Gu-edena to Ninĝirsu’s control ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.53",
      "line_range": "53",
      "translation": "(iv 6) He defeated Unug ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.55",
      "line_range": "55",
      "translation": "(iv 8) He defeated Urim ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.57",
      "line_range": "57",
      "translation": "(iv 10) He defeated Ki-Utu ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.59",
      "line_range": "59",
      "translation": "(iv 12) He conquered Iriaz and killed its ruler ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.63",
      "line_range": "63",
      "translation": "(iv 16) He conquered Mišime ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.65",
      "line_range": "65",
      "translation": "(iv 18) He destroyed Arua ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.67",
      "line_range": "67",
      "translation": "(iv 20) All lands trembled before E-ana-tum , whose name was proclaimed by Ninĝirsu ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.72",
      "line_range": "72",
      "translation": "(iv 25) In the year when the king of Akšak rebelled , E-ana-tum , whose name was proclaimed by Ninĝirsu , repelled Zuzu , king of Akšak , from the Antasura of Ninĝirsu until Akšak and destroyed ( his city ) ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.84",
      "line_range": "84",
      "translation": "(v 9) Then E-ana-tum , whose own name is E-ana-tum , ( but ) whose ... name is Luma , dug a new canal for Ninĝirsu and named it for him as \" Lumagin-dug \"."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.95",
      "line_range": "95",
      "translation": "(v 20) As a sign of her love to him , Inana gave the kingship of Kiš in addition to the rulership of Lagaš to E-ana-tum , who submits to the orders of Ninĝirsu , E-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.107",
      "line_range": "107",
      "translation": "(vi 6) Elam trembled before E-ana-tum and he made the Elamite return into his land ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.110",
      "line_range": "110",
      "translation": "(vi 9) Kiš trembled before E-ana-tum and he made the king of Akšak return into his land ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.113",
      "line_range": "113",
      "translation": "(vi 12) E-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš , who makes the foreign lands submit to Ninĝirsu , defeated Elam , Subartu and Arawa at the A-suhur canal ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.122",
      "line_range": "122",
      "translation": "(vi 21) He defeated Kiš , Akšak and Mari at the Antasura of Ninĝirsu . He had the Lumagin-dug canal reach ( the Antasura ) for Ninĝirsu , and presented him with it . E-ana-tum , given strenght by Ninĝirsu , built a weir on the Lumagin-dug canal with the use of 3600 gur of 2 ul of bitumen ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.138",
      "line_range": "138",
      "translation": "(vii 14) E-ana-tum , who submits to the orders of Ninĝirsu , and whose personal god is Šul-MUŠxPA , built the great temple of Tiraš for ( Ninĝirsu ) ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001057.145",
      "line_range": "145",
      "translation": "(viii 1) He is the child of Aya-kurgal , ruler of Lagaš ; his grandfather is Ur-Nanše , ruler of Lagaš ."
    }
  ],
